<DOC><DOCNO> AP880408-0118 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-08-88 1346EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Philippines-Protest     04-08 0284</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Philippines-Protest,0295</SECOND><HEAD>Police Disperse Anti-Bases Demonstrators</HEAD><DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Police today dispersed about 800demonstrators who tried to rally in front of the U.S. Embassycalling for the dismantling of American military bases in thecountry.   Police said at least 20 police officers suffered minor injuries.Three demonstrators were arrested, they said.   The demonstrators were negotiating with police officials late inthe afternoon when a group of protesters dashed across the streettowards the embassy.   The police gave chase, using riot clubs, while another groupsucceeded in going to the side of the embassy. Other demonstratorshurled stones at the riot police.   A fire truck opened their water cannons against thedemonstrators who scurried into sidestreets fronting the U.S.embassy.   Earlier, the demonstrators were chanting ``dismantle the U.S.bases'' and ``down with imperialists'' as they arrived near theembassy from a downtown plaza.   Police Col. Conrado Francisco said at least 20 policemensuffered stoning and clubbing injuries.   A rally official who spoke on condition of anonymity said theyhad no figures on how many demonstrators were injured but said twoleaders were apprehended by police.   Police could not immediately confirm the arrest of the twoofficials but said they arrested three other demonstrators.   The United States and the Philippines began talks last Tuesdayon the status of American military bases here. The outcome of thetalks, expected to last three months, will determine whether thegovernment allows the bases to remain after their lease expires in1991.   The six U.S. bases are the largest American installations leftin Southeast Asia.   U.S. Ambassador Nicholas Platt, head of the American negotiatingpanel, says the installations are essential to protect the regionfrom Soviet expansion.</TEXT></DOC>